issue.explanation:
This check flags any block comments which look like they had been intended to be KDoc or javadoc comments instead.

If you really want to use Javadoc-like constructs in a block comment, there's a convention you can use: include `(non-Javadoc)` somewhere in the comment, e.g.
```
  /* (non-Javadoc)
   * @see org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler#setDocumentLocator(org.xml.sax.Locator)
   */
  @Override
  public void setDocumentLocator(Locator locator) {
```
(see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5172841/non-javadoc-meaning)

